About Kelly

I'm originally from Dodge City, KS. I moved to New Mexico in 2019 to pursue school counseling and fell in love with Northern New Mexico. I have 3 dogs and I go hiking with them and my husband any chance I get. I am also an avid skier, trail runner, and just started biking recently. I have a history of over 12 years in mental health, working many years with child and adolescent clients. Most recently I started working on furthering my licenser and have gained more experience with adults and SUDs. I am applying for doctoral programs and I'm always looking for ways to help others and be better at what I do.
